ration\u001b[90m (BP-REL-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] External input is validated at trust boundaries (BP-SEC-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Secrets are not committed to source control (BP-SEC-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] No privileged commands in review context (BP-SEC-003)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Sensitive data is not emitted to logs or traces (BP-SEC-004)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Behavior changes are protected by automated tests (BP-TEST-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Critical paths must have deterministic tests (BP-TEST-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Default automated tests do not require live network dependencies (BP-TEST-003)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Module load paths avoid runtime side effects (JAVASCRIPT-ARCH-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Outbound HTTP requests have explicit cancellation or timeout (JAVASCRIPT-REL-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Promises are awaited, returned, or intentionally observed (JAVASCRIPT-REL-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Child process execution avoids shell injection (JAVASCRIPT-SEC-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Dynamic code evaluation is not fed by untrusted input (JAVASCRIPT-SEC-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Public boundary types avoid `any` (TYPESCRIPT-API-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] External data is not cast directly into trusted types (TYPESCRIPT-ARCH-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Type suppression comments are narrow and justified (TYPESCRIPT-ARCH-002)\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \u001b[90m[ESC] Exit | [ARROWS] Navigate | [PGUP/PGDN] Page | [R] Recheck | [F] Fix | [ENTER] Details\u001b[39m\r\n"]
