and safe for the operation\u001b[90m (BP-REL-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[92m[v] External input is validated at trust boundaries\u001b[90m (BP-SEC-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[92m[v] Secrets are not committed to source control\u001b[90m (BP-SEC-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[93m[~] No privileged commands in review context\u001b[90m (BP-SEC-003)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[92m[v] Sensitive data is not emitted to logs or traces\u001b[90m (BP-SEC-004)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[92m[v] Behavior changes are protected by automated tests\u001b[90m (BP-TEST-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Critical paths must have deterministic tests\u001b[90m (BP-TEST-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Default automated tests do not require live network dependencies\u001b[90m (BP-TEST-003)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Module load paths avoid runtime side effects\u001b[90m (JAVASCRIPT-ARCH-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Outbound HTTP requests have explicit cancellation or timeout\u001b[90m (JAVASCRIPT-REL-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Promises are awaited, returned, or intentionally observed\u001b[90m (JAVASCRIPT-REL-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Child process execution avoids shell injection\u001b[90m (JAVASCRIPT-SEC-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  \u001b[97m[⠇] Dynamic code evaluation is not fed by untrusted input\u001b[90m (JAVASCRIPT-SEC-002)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Public boundary types avoid `any` (TYPESCRIPT-API-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] External data is not cast directly into trusted types (TYPESCRIPT-ARCH-001)\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[90m  [ ] Type suppression comments are narrow and justified (TYPESCRIPT-ARCH-002)\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \u001b[90m[ESC] Exit | [ARROWS] Navigate | [PGUP/PGDN] Page | [R] Recheck | [F] Fix | [ENTER] Details\u001b[39m\r\n"]
