[65.452181, "o", "# OpenShrike Scan Report\r\n\r\n- Bundle: `project-checks`\r\n- Policy version: `2026-05-15`\r\n- Repository: `/home/blazej/Projects/OpenShrike.bugfixes`\r\n- Summary: total `25`, pass `19`, fail `0`, unknown `6`\r\n\r\n## Unknown Checks\r\n\r\n### `bp-api-002-bounded-collection-reads`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped changes only add early no-changes handling and action-state synchronization/deduping; no modified external endpoint or command that returns a growing collection is visible in the reviewed files, so this check cannot be assessed from the available scope.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:908`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1097`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-doc-004-architectural-decisions-recorded`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The diff shows a targeted behavior fix for uncommitted scans and UI state deduplication rather than a clear lasting architectural change. I can't confirm a decision record in the scoped files, and the change does not clearly rise to ADR-level scope.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - If this behavior is meant to define a durable scan-scope policy, add an ADR or design note describing the decision and tradeoffs.\r\n  - If no architectural change was intended, no documentation update is needed.\r\n\r\n### `bp-ops-001-meaningful-health-signals`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped changes are for a scan CLI/session flow and UI, not a deployable long-lived service with liveness/readiness endpoints, so this best-practice check is not clearly applicable from the available evidence.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:25`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:148`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:830`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:777`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-rel-002-retries-are-bounded-and-safe`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped diff does not introduce retry loops, retry libraries, or retry configuration. The visible changes add early no-change guards and corresponding tests, but there is no retry behavior to evaluate for boundedness or side-effect safety.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - If retry logic is added later, bound attempts and add backoff/jitter.\r\n  - Only retry operations that are idempotent or protected against duplicate side effects.\r\n\r\n### `bp-sec-003-no-privileged-review-commands`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped changes only show a Docker-based runtime configuration and scan-scope validation, but they do not expose the actual review runtime or any privileged command usage. No `sudo`, `--privileged`, or equivalent host-mutating review-path behavior is visible in the allowed files, so the review environment cannot be verified from scope alone.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:20`\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:29`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - Expose the review runtime configuration used by automated checks so privileged settings can be verified directly.\r\n  - Keep review scripts and container settings rootless and free of `sudo` or `--privileged` flags.\r\n\r\n### `javascript-sec-001-child-process-avoids-shell-injection`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `unknown`\r\n- Confidence: `LOW`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped code uses `spawn()` with separate argument arrays, including a fixed `docker` executable, but it also contains a generic `spawn(command, args, ...)` wrapper whose command provenance is not visible in the reviewed scope, so shell-injection risk cannot be determined conclusively.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1217`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1496`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - Keep using separate argument arrays and avoid `shell: true` for any child-process calls.\r\n  - Ensure any callers of the generic process wrapper pass allowlisted executable names and fixed argument shapes.\r\n\r\n## Passing Checks\r\n\r\n### `bp-api-001-machine-readable-errors`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The scan CLI now raises a structured `CliError` with stable code `NO_CHANGES_IN_SCOPE` at the uncommitted-scope boundary, and the tests assert callers can read both `code` and `message` programmatically. The same no-changes path is exercised consistently in both direct scan and session flows.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2125`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2130`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:133`"]
[65.452283, "o", "\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:271`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-arch-001-avoid-hidden-cross-module-dependencies`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The changes stay within explicit module boundaries: scan logic adds internal early-exit handling for uncommitted scopes, and the UI state sync is factored into a named exported helper rather than reaching into another module's internals. I do not see a new hidden cross-module dependency in the scoped changes.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2223`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-arch-002-dependency-direction-follows-boundaries`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `MEDIUM`\r\n- Rationale: The diff keeps scan orchestration in `src/lib/scan.ts` and UI state reconciliation in `src/ui/scan-app.tsx`; I do not see application/domain code importing UI, transport, or persistence details. The new helpers stay within their existing layer boundaries.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:401`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:908`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-arch-003-composition-root-owns-wiring`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The changed code does not introduce runtime service location or hidden wiring inside business logic. The new helpers are pure, explicit seams (`syncActionStateWithSessionSnapshot` and `createNoChangesInScopeCliError`), while scan startup remains in the orchestration layer and only performs early validation before continuing.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2223`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-ops-005-environment-agnostic-deployment-config`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The committed runtime config in `.openshrike/project.json` uses generic/local values like a relative config path, repo root, and uncommitted scope; it does not hard-code environment-specific hosts, regions, credentials, or cluster identifiers.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:15`\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:28`\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:29`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-rel-001-outbound-dependencies-have-time-budgets`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The uncommitted changes only add local preflight validation, UI state synchronization, and progress counting; they do not introduce or modify any outbound call, polling loop, or blocking wait without a visible time budget.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2223`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-sec-001-boundary-input-validation`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The uncommitted scan scope boundary now validates the resolved scope before any check execution, runtime loading, or other scan side effects begin, and it fails fast with a dedicated `NO_CHANGES_IN_SCOPE` error. The added tests confirm the rejection path and that no evaluation work is started.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2125`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-sec-002-no-committed-secrets`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped diff only changes scan control flow, UI state synchronization, and tests, plus a non-sensitive parallelism setting. I found no plaintext credentials, API keys, tokens, private keys, or credential-bearing connection strings in the reviewed changes.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `.openshrike/project.json:18`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:401`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:908`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1097`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2116`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1661`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2220`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:312`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:250`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:104`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - No remediation needed\r\n\r\n### `bp-sec-004-sensitive-data-not-logged`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The only telemetry emission in scope writes the scan progress event, and the newly changed status text for the uncommitted-no-changes path is a generic message. The event fields shown here are operational identifiers and counts, with no raw auth headers, tokens, passwords, payment data, or payload bodies emitted.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2101`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2071`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - Keep telemetry limited to operational identifiers and counts.\r\n  - Avoid adding raw payload or credential fields to scan progress events.\r\n\r\n### `bp-test-001-behavior-changes-covered`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The behavior changes in scan scope handling, early no-changes failure, optimistic action-state syncing, and unique in-progress counting are each paired with focused automated tests in the same diff. The production changes are directly exercised by new or updated tests that assert the new error path, status label, snapshot sync semantics, and deduped progress counts.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1680`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:280`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:315`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-test-002-deterministic-tests`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The changed tests avoid wall-clock timing and sleep-based coordination. The session test waits on an explicit predicate (`updates.waitFor`) and then asserts state after the signal, while the new scan tests mock scope resolution and assert a deterministic progress sequence; the UI tests are pure state-transform assertions.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:235`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:271`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:124`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:315`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `bp-test-003-default-tests-no-live-network`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The changed default test files are hermetic: they mock policy, scope, runtime, config, evaluator, logger, and fix-runtime dependencies, and the new cases use temp repos or pure UI helpers only. No real URLs, cloud resources, or ambient credentials are visible in scope.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:21`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:67`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:16`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:1`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:267`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `javascript-arch-001-no-module-load-side-effects`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The uncommitted changes add and call helpers only from explicit scan/session functions and UI state reducers; no new top-level statement starts work, performs I/O, registers listeners, or launches background activity at module import time.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:390`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:900`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1090`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2071`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1649`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2210`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `javascript-rel-001-http-requests-have-abort-or-timeout`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped diff only changes scan-scope handling, UI state synchronization, and related tests. No outbound HTTP client usage, fetch/Axios/got/undici calls, or shared network client configuration is introduced or modified in the review scope.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1100`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - No action needed for this check.\r\n  - If future changes add outbound network calls, bound them with an explicit timeout or AbortSignal.\r\n\r\n### `javascript-rel-002-promises-are-awaited-or-observed`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The changed async paths keep promise-producing work awaited or returned, and the new snapshot/state helpers do not introduce detached promise execution. The added scan-scope resolution and runtime loading paths explicitly await their promises, and the session startup path awaits preparation before continuing.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:398`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:439`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:1101`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1658`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:236`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:115`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `javascript-sec-002-no-eval-on-untrusted-input`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped changes only add scan-scope validation, progress/status handling, and state-sync tests. I found no `eval`, `new Function`, `vm`, or equivalent dynamic code execution in the scoped files, and no user-influenced content is routed into runtime code generation.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:404`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:911`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2223`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n  - `tests/scan-app.test.ts:315`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - No remediation needed; keep dynamic execution APIs out of these scan and UI code paths.\r\n  - If future code generation is added, ensure the source is fixed and repository-owned, not derived from scan input or other external data.\r\n\r\n### `typescript-api-001-public-boundary-types-avoid-any`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `MEDIUM`\r\n- Rationale: The changed exported boundaries use concrete typed contracts (`ScanHooks`, `ScanSessionSnapshot`, `createNativeScanSession`, `syncActionStateWithSessionSnapshot`, and `deriveProgressCounts`), and the scoped diff does not introduce `any` in those public signatures.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:89`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:111`\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:148`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:1671`\r\n  - `src/ui/scan-app.tsx:2210`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n"]
[65.452303, "o", "\r\n### `typescript-arch-001-external-data-not-cast-to-trusted-types`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `MEDIUM`\r\n- Rationale: The scoped changes do not introduce direct assertions from external payloads into trusted domain types; the new uncommitted-scope path is guarded by a runtime check before execution continues, and the added tests exercise the failure path instead of relying on casts.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - `src/lib/scan.ts:2125`\r\n  - `tests/scan-session.test.ts:253`\r\n  - `tests/scan.test.ts:107`\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n\r\n### `typescript-arch-002-ts-ignore-is-narrow-and-justified`\r\n- Version: `0.1.0`\r\n- Status: `pass`\r\n- Confidence: `HIGH`\r\n- Rationale: No @ts-ignore, @ts-expect-error, or broad type-suppression comments were added in the scoped changes, so there is no suppression to assess for scope or justification.\r\n- Evidence:\r\n  - none\r\n- Remediation:\r\n  - none\r\n"]
